It is long story but I got to hang out with Poncho and Chris from RBD. We partied from 12pm to 5am. It was amazing!!! They were super nice and terrific dancers!! We all got to talk to them alot we all became good friends and were on a first name basis. We went to Mangos on Ocean Dr.. Thanks Margo for the fake ID, you are the best!! Lov Ya!! Oh and I now love Chris, he has really cute personality more compatible with me than Poncho plus he is also hot.. Poncho is still cute too though!

Yesturday at Premios Juventud I was able to only work as "Talent Escort" (guiding lost celebrities), but as press ( i got ask alot of questions!!!) allowing me to see pretty much everyone at the awards.... My first celebrity was cute Shelbie Bruce from Spanglish with Adam Sandler I also saw, yes yet again, Luis Fonsi. I walked him to the stage. He was super nice as usual. I also escorted Carlos Arroyo (Basketball, NBA, Puerto Rican), he was super nice, he even put his arm around me:) Also, Christian De LA Fuente (Hot soap opera star) Out of all the people saw the ones that impacted me and therefore remember are: RBD!!!!! I have a brilliant anecdote which I'll tell you at the end Chayanne- gorgeous DADDY YANKEE- super "humilde"- del barrio de PR Enrique Iglesias- not bad in person, super nice Laura Pausini Olga Tanon Frankie J Barbara Bermudos - Primer Impacto Jaguares- mexican rolling stones Wisin y Yandel -reggeaton Lunny Tunes- reggeaton Las Senadoras- i actually escorted them to the bathroom and then to the stage Ivy Queen- reggeaton Anais- Spanish American Idol- "the latin Beyonce" Obie Bermudez- linda stuck up although Puerto Rican Sissy - from Sabado Gigante I actually helped her with her cellphone Christian Castro- stuck up, ugly, gay, but has a good voice Miss PR- super pretty well-deserved 2nd runner up position at Miss Universe La 5ta Estacion- GREAT GROUP, I LOVE THEIR CD!! And I'm pretty sure I forgot a few artists that I also liked... Ok now for the highlight of my evening.... As press Sylvi and I sat in the first row with Gigi in the back (next to the Univision camera).. Alot of artists were nice enough to give a shout out to the University of Miami at our resquest like Jaguares, Barbara Bermudo, ANNNDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDDD RBD!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! OK Sylvi asks them to give a shout out to the University of Miami and as Christopher was about to do it I shout to them that it was towards the only woman camera person, Chris gives his shout out and then PONCHO (yes my Poncho) gives a special shout to Gigi in the back!!!! It was super cool he heard him. NOW, when I was walking back stage to get my stuff and go home I run into PONCHO and I thank him for his comment on Gigi and he was super nice and started talking to me, showing me his award (which he had in his hand), he asked of what were the cool places to party in Miami ( i said Mansion b/c i know that's were the famous people go), and then out of NOWHERE he leans in and gives a KISSSSSSSSSS HUGGGGGGGGGG. I almost died!!! He was soo great!!! Seriously this is my new "Luis Fonsi".... So there, this was a night to remember and seriously it's so weird how i always get to meet and talk to to ALL my platonic loves (Dean Cain, Luis Fonsi and now, Poncho)!!!!!

That's right. For those who know me know that I was desperately in love with Luis Fonsi, but there is a new man in my life and is name is Poncho Herrera. He is sooooo hottt and can sing too. Yes people there is trend here.... I'm into musicians.... And I know Margo doesn't like the name Poncho, he also goes by Alfonso. Luis Fonsi Is from Puerto Rico Poncho Is from Mexico

Hello everyone! Hope everyone's summer is going great. Mine has had its ups and downs. Right now I am in Ecuador w/ my Mom. I had the great opportunity to go to Banos, a small town in the mountains of Ecuador. It was so cool!! For those of you who know me know that I LOVE mountains, and therefore to me this place was heaven. I got to a see the Chumbarazo volcano, SO COOL!! I went with my very good friend, Patricio and his family. They were great, they made the trip that much better. 

Here is the link to some pics I took while on the trip.. PLEASE CHECK THEM OUT, SO YOU CAN SEE HOW BEAUTIFUL THIS PLACE IS!!

http://www.kodakgallery.com/BrowsePhotos.jsp?&collid=90636525109&page=1&sort_order=0

luv always,

BJ

The news coming from Brad Pitt's brother that he and Angelina are having a baby togther totally stunned me.  I can understand that he desperately wants children and that he may have fallen for angelina, but couldn't have at least waited til the divorce was final with Jen?? I find it very hard to believe on how someone can move on so rapidly like the previous relationship ment nothing to him. I mean seriously poor Jen. And I don't think its Angelina's fault either, its all on Brad. 

I'm probably overreacting, but the situation looks very disturbing to me.  I wouldn't do that.
"If u find this, LFs twin, I just wanted to say I'm sorry from the bottom of my heart"- BJ

Once again I meet the love of my life. It's as if we were meant to be-soulmates! All the people that know me know that I could be anywhere in the world and Luis Fonsi will form part of my life. I have heard him on the radio like 3 times already since I've been here in Ecuador and he's not even popular here. Really. And I not only hear is music everywhere, I see him everywhere too. He must think I'm some sort of stalker but I'm not...  But don't we make the cutuest couple :) You be the judge...

http://i7.photobucket.com/albums/y263/brenda_style/387bb6c9.jpg

(please click the link to see pic b/c image was too large to put on actual message; sorry)


If one day we do really get together (in this life anything is possible!) this pic will prove as forsight to the future. And newleyweds Margo and Jude will come to our wedding and our baby shower.. LOL

Summer school is finally over. Hopefully I did okay.  I've been looking foward to my real vacation for a long time. I leave for Guayaquil tomorrow where I'll spend 3 weeks with my mom. I'm going to be going to Quito (the capital of Ecuador) and Bogota, Colombia for a couple of days. That'll be fun and different. I'm also going to the beach a lot which I honestely haven't been in months. I'm going to be online a lot, so everyone is welcome to email or aim me. And I'll be updating my lj to let everyone know how its going. 

Best Wishes and I hope everyone keeps having a great fun summer. :)

Believe it or not when I was in 7th and 8th, I was obsessed with Lois and Clark: the new adventures of Superman. I had every episode taped on VHS. I would watch it everyday on TNT syndication. Many of you may think why in the hell I would like this show so much, but I did, I thought it was greatness. And I was in love with Dean Cain. I even got to meet him when he came to film a movie in PR called "Flight of Fancy". He was so nice and HOT!! Well, anyway, naturally I got super excited when they released the first season on DVD. I bought it as soon as I could and now I can't stop watching it. It brings me so much joy and good memories!!

PR may be a small country, but we are always in something.... Puerto Rico is RUNNER UP MISS UNIVERSE 2005: YEY!!! :) The winner was Canada. I personally liked Mexico, Dominican Republic, and PR,of coarse. Canada's noise is kinda weird. My pick would have been Mexico-she was pretty and gave a nice answer. Well, anyway, whatever. Toodles, BJ
